The Overseer of the Kaduna State Muslim Pilgrims Welfare Board, Malam Sani Musa, is dead. Musa died in a motor accident along Kaduna-Abuja highway. The Board Public Relation Officer, Malam Salisu Anchau, who confirmed the incident to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) said the accident occurred at about 10:30 am along Kaduna-Abuja highway. He added that the deceased would be buried after funeral prayers to be held by 5:30 pm at Sardauna Memorial College Kaduna. Musa was appointed by Gov. Nasir El-Rufia as Overseer of the board on January 12, 2020.